BSE - POLAND (02): CORRECTION
*********************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Fri, 10 May 2002 16:45:07 -0400
From: David_Hutto@BIOGEN.COM

This report makes reference to BSE being related to human Creutzfield-Jacob
disease, and that 100 people have died of this disease. They are referring
to variant Creuzfield-Jacob disease (vCJD), not CJD.
--
David L. Hutto DVM, PhD, D-ACVP
Principal Pathologist
Veterinary and Comparative Pathology
Biogen, Inc.
14 Cambridge Center
Cambridge, MA 02142, USA
<david_hutto@biogen.com>
[Thank you, David. We should have pointed out that that part of the news
report was incorrect. - Mod.JW]
